{"word":"χατέω","slug":"χατέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>χατέω</b></el> <el>(χᾰτέω,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a> <i>to crave, long</i> to do a thing, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>; <a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a>, <el>χατέοντί περ ἔμπης</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <el>μάλα περ χατέουσα</el> <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to crave, have need of</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}